California Power Exchange Corporation Original Sheet No. 2M FERC Rate Schedule No. 1 Superseding Original Sheet No. 2L
CALPX WIND-UP CHARGE
The California Power Exchange Corporation (CalPX) wind-up charge is designed to recover the expenses of CalPX winding up its operations for the period July 1, 2021 through December 31, 2021 (Rate Period 39). The wind-up expenses include, but are not limited to, payroll, telephone, IT support, building costs, insurance, temporary labor, FERC and non-FERC litigation and legal costs, and miscellaneous expenses. The total amount of such expenses is $2,174,624 for Rate Period 39. The total cash shortfall for Rate Period 39 is projected to be $1,414,727.
Reserved Amount
The amount of $1,414,727 (Reserve Amount) shall be reserved and transferred from the CalPX Settlement Clearing Account to cover the projected expenses for Rate Period 39. To the extent any of the Reserve Amount is not required for CalPX's wind-up expenses in Rate Period 39, the unused amount shall be carried over to the subsequent rate period and reflected as cash on hand. To the extent there is any unused amount at the conclusion of CalPX's last rate schedule, pursuant to the allocation methodology used to attribute expenses the unused amount shall be credited to CalPX's participants as part of the financial clearing stage in accordance with FERC's orders in Docket Nos. EL00-95-000 et al.
Billings
For the Reserve Amount that CalPX is permitted to withdraw from the Settlement Clearing Account for Rate Period 39, CalPX will bill its participants pursuant to the allocation methodology for Going Forward Costs set forth on Attachment A of the Rate Case Settlement Agreement. Such funding for Rate Period 39 shall be from funds in the Settlement Clearing Account or payments in cash from CalPX participants and shall be accounted for via adjustments to each participant's Account Summary Statement.
CalPX is authorized to establish, maintain, transfer or close bank accounts and other banking facilities or arrangements it deems necessary or convenient for the operation of its billing and payment systems. CalPX may instruct the bank to debit the Settlement Clearing Account and transfer to the relevant CalPX operating account the Reserve Amount as CalPX's wind-up expenses in Rate Period 38.
Future Rate Filings
Pursuant to the terms of the Rate Case Settlement Agreement in Docket Nos. ER02- 2234-000 et al., and as extended by the Commission on July 2, 2007 in Docket No. ER07-861- 000 and on May 3, 2010 in Docket No. ER10-905-000, CalPX reserves the right to file for cost recovery in subsequent six-month periods.
This tariff sheet is subject to the terms and conditions of the Rate Case Settlement Agreement, including but not limited to any provisions regarding allocation of possible proceeds from litigation or insurance.
Issued by: David K. Gottlieb, Interim Chief Executive Officer Effective: July 1, 2021 Issued on: April 30, 2021
